title: Shift Summary, Mon, 31 Jan 2022.
text: Summary: AccPhy as scheduled, no machine problems. Injector: LTB steering early in the shift, no changes saved, recovery OK. SPARK BPM program in LTB and BTS lines; recovery OK. SPEAR: Stored beam in SPEAR coasting most of the shift. Dumped near 1430 for BL 12-1 work. 5mA in a solo bucket for BxB program at end of the shift. BLs: BLs are shut. BL 12-1 TSR continues with hardware in a Watch and Wait state.

DAY-Shift Report 1/31/2022 Mon
text: PROGRAM: SPEAR to ACC PHY delivering various currents as AP program dictates. BEAMLINES: All closed. 0600 BL12-0 keyed offline per RSWCF 2190. 1500 BL12-1 is online and waiting for a replica of the faults from 1/26/2022 until end of AP program. FAULTS: 0607 BL5/6/12 PPS/BCS fault, expected due to RSWCF 2190 work. 0907 BL14 Pr2 fault. BL14-3 Helium tripped for low vessel pressure. Expected due to staff working in the hutch. 1321 BL10 Pr2 fault. LCW7 circuit tripped below 68 inches H2O setpoint. Adjusted flow from 71 to 97 inches H2O. Fault reset at 1331. 1430 Repeat of 0607 fault, expected due to RSWCF 2190 work. EXPERIMENTS: 1010-1100 BL10-2 user support. Helped user navigate to the correct directory to download his data. Updated written instructions. OPERATIONS: 0750 Filled LHS dewar at LN fill station. 0940 BL9-0 hutch opened for replacement of fluro lights. MPSWCF 204 opened for BL17-0 Pr1 faults troubleshooting. MPSWCF 205 opened for BL15-2 IG1 MPS interlock, 5 second delay added to BL15-2 IG1 fault. This in response to multiple faults over the past few days. 1500 Pico scope loaned out to O. Mueller.

title: Some events have transpired
text: -tried Eloss -Eloss tripped BLMs, so tried abort -abort killed the GUI and thus didn't set magnets properly, so loaded most recent score ("start swing", 15:59), UNDH and LTUH-->BSYH regions (rushed decision -- didn't need to load the latter region) -somehow, despite the SCORE claiming magnet settings of 14.45 GeV, the magnets trimmed to 14.25 GeV -reloaded SCORE from 15:58, magnets recovered to 14.45 GeV Plot below shows that loading the first SCORE did not set the BCON to 14.45 GeV, but the second SCORE did. The bends also have not lost their standardize bit. Pulse intensity is slightly reduced -- from about 1 mJ to about 0.95 mJ.

title: FACET 11-8
text: 11-8 Worked on getting station on and running, Dropped BV all the down Punched station on until it would run for about 10 minutes then tried to slowly raise up to spec, but kept tripping off on over currents, ran good at 288kv, Could only get it up to 303KV but station running nice for now, Don't know if there is process work needed on Klystron or if the T20 taps might have to be raised for more D Q ing...OBTW

title: FACET 16-4
text: 16-4 Put sta in Maint until VVS can be reset, Lowered Eres about 3V and disabled triggers using VGC so that when VVS reset and sta punched on we might avoid tripping the VVS again, If station breaker trips when punched on from green light and triggers added then the Thyratron could be shorted as the res has been lowered already, if Mod comes back ok then run for an hour and range Thy until stable
